      • checkLanguageConsistency

        private static java.lang.String checkLanguageConsistency(java.lang.String firstLanguage,
                                                         java.lang.String secondLanguage)
        Checks two languages for consistency, returning the consistent language, or throwing an IllegalStateException if the languages are inconsistent.

        Two languages are consistent if they are equal, or if one is null.

        Parameters:

        secondLanguage - The second language.
        Returns:
        The consistent language.

      • checkContentTypeConsistency

        private static int checkContentTypeConsistency(int firstType,
                                               int secondType)
        Checks two adaptation set content types for consistency, returning the consistent type, or throwing an IllegalStateException if the types are inconsistent.

        Two types are consistent if they are equal, or if one is C.TRACK_TYPE_UNKNOWN. Where one of the types is C.TRACK_TYPE_UNKNOWN, the other is returned.

        Parameters:
        firstType - The first type.
        secondType - The second type.
        Returns:
        The consistent type.
